OL,3,CShip's captain guilty of manslaughter
OL,4,Cafter North Sea crash
OL,6,FA ship's captain has been found guilty
OL,7,Fof killing a crew member in a crash
OL,8,Fwith an oil tanker off the coast of
OL,9,FEast Yorkshire.
OL,11,FRussian Vladimir Motin had been on
OL,12,Fsole watch duty when the Solong
OL,13,Fcollided with the Stena Immaculate
OL,14,Fanchored near the Humber Estuary last
OL,15,F10 March.
OL,17,FFilipino national Mark Angelo Pernia,
OL,18,F38, who was working on the Solong's
OL,19,Fbow, died in the fire, although his
OL,20,Fbody was never recovered.
