OL,3,CShip's captain guilty of manslaughter
OL,4,Cafter North Sea crash
OL,6,FMotin was responsible for multiple
OL,7,Ffailures in the lead-up to the tragedy
OL,8,Fand then lied about what took place on
OL,9,Fthe bridge, it was alleged.
OL,11,FThe Stena Immaculate was visible on
OL,12,Fthe Solong's radar display for 36
OL,13,Fminutes before impact, yet Motin did
OL,14,Fnothing to steer away from the
OL,15,Fcollision course, the prosecution said.
OL,17,FHe failed to summon help, slow down,
OL,18,Fsound the alarm to alert crews of both
OL,19,Fships, or instigate a crash stop as a
OL,20,Flast resort, the prosecution said.
