OL,6,FJurors heard a lengthy silence from
OL,7,Fthe bridge of the Solong before it
OL,8,Fcrashed into the oil tanker at a speed
OL,9,Fof 15.2 knots. A full minute elapsed
OL,10,Fbefore Motin was heard to react.
OL,12,FMotin and the remaining Solong crew
OL,13,Fabandoned ship and were brought ashore
OL,14,Fin Grimsby where the defendant
OL,15,Fmessaged his wife, saying he would be
OL,16,F"guilty".
OL,18,FIn his defence, Motin denied he had
OL,19,Fbeen asleep or had left his post on
OL,20,Fthe bridge.
OL,26,@xD@AOUxD@HO]
