OL,6,FHe told jurors that he held off taking
OL,7,Faction when he saw the Stena
OL,8,FImmaculate dead ahead because it was
OL,9,Fmoving slowly but unpredictably.
OL,11,FHe then made a "mistake" and pressed
OL,12,Fthe wrong button when he tried to take
OL,13,Fthe Solong out of autopilot and steer
OL,14,Faway from one nautical mile away.
OL,16,FNot realising the error, he told
OL,17,Fjurors that he proceeded to stop and
OL,18,Frestart the steering gear to no
OL,19,Feffect, thinking the Solong could have
OL,20,Fdeveloped a rudder fault experienced
OL,21,Fby sister ship, Sanskip Express.
