OL,6,FMotin said he decided against a crash
OL,7,Fstop because he feared the Solong
OL,8,Fwould collide with the accommodation
OL,9,Fblock, killing the American tanker
OL,10,Fcrew.
OL,12,FHe told jurors: "I thought the
OL,13,Fdistance to stop is not enough. I put
OL,14,Flife of American crew in danger if I
OL,15,Fhit accommodation."
OL,17,FThe prosecution suggested Motin had
OL,18,Flied about what happened to "get back
OL,19,Fto his wife" in Russia and gave
OL,20,Fdiffering accounts to police and
OL,21,Fjurors.
